	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hello,
<br />
<br />This may seem like a pretty dumb question, but I need to ask it.  I'm currently in the process of making some repro carts, and was wondering if it were possible to use burned chips of a game that originally used TLROM onto a TSROM donor cart.  Since the game wouldn't be using the 8K of W-RAM, wouldn't that still be okay?
<br />
<br />I know that there are differences between the 3, but if they're using the same mapper and I rewire the cart properly to take the EPROMS, would they work?  I just seem to have way too many SMB3 carts laying around that I wouldn't mind putting to good use <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />.
<br />
<br />Thanks!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


